State MSM Profile: Maine

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Maine

An estimated 15,070 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Maine in 2013, representing 0.3% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 511,631 adult men of Maine, 2.9% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Maine resided in counties within medium or small metropolitan areas (64.9%). No MSM in Maine resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Maine, 2013

MSM in Maine Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Maine, Cumberland County had the largest population of MSM at 4,378, representing 29.1% of all MSM in the state. Cumberland County also had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Maine at 4.1%. This was greater than the percentage for Maine as a whole, which was 2.9% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Maine Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Portland-South Portland Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Portland-South Portland MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Maine at 7,260, or 48.2% of all MSM in the state. Of the 196,162 adult men in Portland-South Portland, an estimated 3.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Lewiston-Auburn Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Lewiston-Auburn MSA had a population of 1,290 MSM, or 8.6% of all MSM in Maine. Of the 40,307 adult men in Lewiston-Auburn, an estimated 3.2% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Bangor Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Bangor MSA had a population of 1,234 MSM, or 8.2% of all MSM in Maine. Of the 60,474 adult men in Bangor, an estimated 2.0% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
